    • takeFromStack

      int takeFromStack(Predicate<ItemStack> predicate, boolean simulate, int count, InventoryUtility.ItemStackCounter store, ItemStack source, ItemStack filter, EntityPlayerMP player)
      Extract a particular type of item. The extractor can choose to not return all items contained within this item as long as it makes sense, but the author should inform the player of this.

      Whether this method does recursive extraction is at the discretion of implementor.

      Parameters:
      predicate - the main filtering predicate. never null. It's assumed predicate always returns true on filter, if that is not null
      simulate - true if only query but does not actually remove
      store - where to store extracted items. Should increment the
      source - from where an extraction should be attempted
      filter - stack to extract. should not be mutated! match the NBT tag using EXACT mode. might be null.
      player - executor of extraction, or null if from a machine
      Returns:
      amount extracted, or -1 if this is not implemented
